snippet: The victim of the Upper West Side robbery, a bartender who had been drinking, had no recollection of what had happened.
abstract: Michael Wilson Crime Scene column recounts efforts by Manhattan bartender to trace events that led to his waking up in bed with two front teeth missing and a series of fraudulent activity on his missing ATM card; holds that story is cruel reminder that danger remains in New York City's safer neighborhoods.
lead_paragraph: The victim of the Upper West Side robbery, a bartender who had been drinking, had no recollection of what had happened.

headline.seo: Bartender Robbed and Beaten, but Can’t Recall How
